        "text": "King Albert met Queen Paola in Rome at a reception given by the then Belgian ambassador. The ambassador was a collector of Flemish Primitive paintings and had a work by the Flemish Primitive artist Dirk Bouts in his collection.\n\nWhile he was admiring the painting the then Prince Albert saw what he described as “a beautiful apparition” enter the room. This was the woman that would later become his wife.\n\nPaola herself was not so impressed that evening. In an interview with commercial television she said he main concern that night was to go to bed early. However, protocol requires guests to stay at an event until a prince (or other royals) have left). Sadly for her Prince Albert stuck around, rulling out and early night.\n\nOnce back in Belgium, Prince Albert sent Paola a postcard and dates followed.\n\nThen the time came for the then young prince to attempt take things to the next level. Prince Albert was very unsure of what the reaction would be.\n\n\"I rented a little Italian car. A sky-blue Alfa Romeo. She got behind the wheel. I sat next to her and started explaining that I liked her. And if she agreed, maybe we could go a bit further. She had her 2 hands on the wheel, so she had no choice but to drive on,\" King jokes.\n\nPaola didn't not say yes, she didn't say no either. She just asked for time for them to get to know each other. This they did by amongst other things staying with Paola's sister in Florence"
